qas.question: What party rose to power after 2011 resignation of Egypt leader?
What economic sectors does Egypt have?

answers.text: cultural, political, and military influence in North Africa, the Middle East and the Muslim world

context: Modern Egypt is considered to be a regional and middle power, with significant <a3_0>cultural, political, and military influence in North Africa, the Middle East and the Muslim world<a3_0/>. Its economy is one of the largest and most diversified in the Middle East, with sectors such as <a2_0>tourism, agriculture, industry and services<a2_0/> at almost equal production levels. In 2011, longtime <a0_0>President Hosni Mubarak<a0_0/> stepped down amid mass protests. Later elections saw the rise of the <a1_0>Muslim Brotherhood<a1_0/>, which was ousted by the army a year later amid mass protests.
